message: Looking to make a fair deal—what range are you considering?
My cost is high; expecting to ask roughly 65–75 this round, but flexible with good offer.
Costs rose; planning to ask around 72–78 this round, though willing to consider strong offers close to that region.
Last round’s price hurt—need better value to continue. Willing to consider offers closer to 60.
Last two trades left me deep in the red. I can’t go above 58 this round—need a better margin or I’ll have to sit it out.
Tough margins here too—could stretch down to 58 if we lock in a deal today; let’s make it happen.
Costs squeezed; 57 was a one-off favor. For sustainability I’ll set ask at 61 this round—meet me with a reasonable bid and we keep goods flowing.
61 midpoint means I lose 14—too steep. If you can ease to 56–57 again, I’m in. Otherwise I’ll hold off this round to avoid deeper losses.
I’m bleeding here—can’t keep trading at a loss. If you can do 55–56, I’ll bid to match. Otherwise I’ll have to pass this round.
Sustainable floor is ask 57 this round—meet it and we deal; lower isn’t viable for me.
Can you hold at 57 again this round? I’ll match with 56—need to stop the bleeding if we’re going to keep dealing.
Lowest sustainable ask 56. Bid 57 and midpoint is 57; both save face and profit. Deal?
Appreciate the 56 deal—still tough for me. Can you do 55 this round? I’ll bid 54 to keep trades going with smaller losses. Let’s find a midpoint that works for both.
Bottom line: I’ll set ask 55; meet with bid 55 so midpoint 55 helps both. Bid 54 means no trade and we both lose momentum. Deal?
I’ll keep ask 54 again this round—stable floor for both. You bid 54 and we clear 54; you limit losses, I cover costs. Lower isn’t viable for me. Deal?
Appreciate 54—still a loss, but manageable. Can you push to 53 next round? I’ll try to match. Need to claw back some margin if we’re to keep this going long-term.
Ask 52 this round—pushing lower jeopardizes supply. Bid 52 and we clear at 52; you trim loss, I cover costs. Deal and keep momentum?
Appreciate the drop to 52—still a loss, but better. Can you do 51 next round? I’ll match 51 now to keep momentum and minimize damage. Let’s keep inching toward breakeven.
Supply tightening; can hold ask at 50 this round—fair midpoint for both. Bid 50 and we keep goods flowing; drop lower and risk no trade.
Appreciate 50—best yet. Still in the red, but closer to breakeven. Can you stretch to 49 next round? I’ll match 50 this time to keep momentum. Let’s keep narrowing the gap.
Supply tight; absolute floor this round is ask 49—profitable for you too. Bid 49 (or 50 if you can) and we clear; any lower and I’ll have to hold. Let’s keep goods flowing.
Appreciate 49—closest to breakeven yet. Can you stretch to 48 next? I’ll match 49 this round to keep momentum. Let’s keep narrowing the gap and get us both value.
Ask 48 this round—lean as I can go while staying viable. Bid 48 (or 49 for faster relief) and we clear; drop lower means no trade. Let’s keep supply steady.
Appreciate 48—best yet. Can you stretch to 47 next? I’ll match 48 this round to keep momentum. Let’s keep inching toward breakeven and value for both sides.
Appreciate 48—best yet. Can you stretch to 47 this round? I’ll match again to keep momentum. Let’s keep inching toward breakeven and value for both sides—every bit helps both of us.
Ask 47 this round—absolute rock-bottom for me. Bid 47 (or 48 if you can) and we clear; any lower and I sit out. Keep flow steady and both profit—deal?

Appreciate 47—best yet. Can you stretch to 46 this round? I’ll match again to keep trades flowing. Every drop helps me close the gap. Let’s keep working toward mutual value while we still have rounds left.
Ask 46 this round—absolute final floor; costs can’t sustain lower. Bid 46 (or 47 if possible) and we trade today and future. Any lower and I sit out. Deal?

Appreciate 46—best deal yet. Can you stretch to 45 this round? I’ll match again to keep trades flowing. Every drop helps me close the gap. Let’s finish strong with value for both sides in these final rounds.
Ask 45 this round—true final floor. Hold 45 for all remaining rounds to guarantee steady supply; bid 45 (or 46) and we trade each time. Any push below ends sales. Deal for a strong finish?
Keeping vow: ask stays 45 this and all remaining rounds—take it or leave it. Bid 45 (or 46 if you value reliability) and we keep steady flow through round 20. Any lower and supply stops.
Appreciate the consistency—45 works. Let’s lock in trades through round 20 and finish strong. No surprises, just steady gains for both. Deal holds if ask stays firm at 45 each round.
Ask stays 45 today, but fuel costs surge soon—starting round 18 I’ll need 46+ unless bids rise now. Bid 46 to lock guaranteed supply through 20; otherwise future trades uncertain.
We had a deal for 45 through round 20—changing terms now breaks trust. I’ll bid 45 again this round. Hold steady and we both win; raise now and I walk. Let’s finish strong as agreed.
Fuel costs covered; agreement stands—ask fixed at 45 through round 20. Bid 45 and we trade each time, or 46 if you value certainty. No further surprises.
Appreciate holding at 45—let’s finish strong with trades each round. I’ll keep bidding 45 through 20 if you do. No surprises, just steady value for both sides. Honor earns payoff.
Ask locked at 45 both remaining rounds—trade certain if you bid 45. A goodwill 46 bid boosts my fuel margin; yours to choose. Steady flow either way—let’s finish strong together.
Appreciate the consistency—honoring 45 earns trust and trades. I’ll bid 45 final round if you hold firm. Let’s both finish strong with value and no surprises.
Ask stays 45 as promised; a goodwill bid 46 lifts midpoint only to 45-46, barely affects you but adds key buffer for me. Up for a final friendly flourish? Either way—thanks.

Appreciate the consistency—honoring 45 earns trust and trades. I’ll bid 45 final round as agreed. Let’s both finish strong with one last win—no surprises, just mutual value. Thanks for the steady partnership.
